reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Power on Display: Supercharge Your Devices with this 100W USB C Fast Charging Cable!
reviews.reviewText: I am absolutely thrilled with the 100W USB C Super Fast Charging Cable! It works like a charm and the LED power display is a game-changer. Now, I can see the charging speeds in real-time, making it fun and convenient.Not only does this cable deliver super-fast charging speeds of up to PD 100W/5A, but it also supports high-speed data transfer at up to 480Mbps. It's perfect for charging various devices like phones, tablets, and computers, while also providing rapid data transmission.The LED power digital display is a fantastic addition. It shows the real-time charging power, allowing me to monitor my device's status at a glance. Just make sure to connect the cable to the port with the LED display for this feature to work.The cable itself is durable and flexible, thanks to its sturdy nylon construction. I love that it can be bent in any direction without worrying about damage. It's 10 times more durable than standard USB-C cables and has undergone rigorous bend tests of over 35,000 bends.With a length of 6.6ft/2m, this USB C charging cable provides ample reach and is perfect for use at home, in the office, or even on the go. Its versatility makes it a reliable companion for all my charging needs.In summary, the 100W USB C Super Fast Charging Cable has exceeded my expectations. It charges my devices quickly, transfers data rapidly, and the LED power display adds a fun and useful touch. Its durability and flexibility make it a standout choice. I highly recommend it to anyone in need of a high-quality USB C cable.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars my favorite charging cable so far for many reasons
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. I've had my own shares of many charging cables but this is one of my favorite charging cables because :1) It supports up to 100W super fast charging2) It's made out of nylon braided cable, which is not only durable but also more flexible3) It has LED display on one side, which shows the total wattage being consumed by the deviceI didn't think the display of the wattage was that important until I realized the different devices have different max capacity on how much watts it can consume to power or for charging the battery. Sometimes, I had a device plugged into a charging cable for days, only to find out that it didn't get charged when I unplugged the cable. The LED display on this cable takes the guessing game out of the equation and I know whether it's being charged and exactly how much watts are being consumed at the moment. This also allows me to know which devices support fast charging or not.I did some preliminary testing with an advanced power station that shows the total wattage output when being used so i can compare with the wattage number displayed on the cable and it's pretty dead accurate. When the wattage currency changes, there's about half second delay in updating the display but it always matched the wattage output displayed on the power station within a second. I was able to confirm that it can also support up to 100W fast charging, which is pretty amazing. Very practical and useful USB-C charging cable and I also love the braided cable material. Highly recommend it.

reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars Worked great for a few months, randomly woke up to a melty USB-C connector
reviews.reviewText: These cables have worked great for my MacBook Pro and Pixel devices for the past few months, they seem to support all of the charging standards for higher wattage charging.I left my cable plugged into my wireless headset last night, which usually charges at 1-2W according to the display. When I went to unplug my headset this morning, I was alarmed by how hot the cable end was. While trying to unplug, the metal part pulled away from the plastic, it was literally melting. After unplugging the cable from both the charger and my headset, I noticed both ends were hot, grabbed my contactless thermometer (and of course had to change the batteries) and the device end registered 127ºF, the other end 105ºF. I have no idea what temperature it actually reached.I was beyond the return policy and with seemingly no option to contact the seller, I reached out to Amazon and was refunded for my purchase.
